-- Generated by `supabase db pull` after applying 20260507000000.
--
-- The CLI produced a single line: `drop extension if exists "pg_net";`
-- That is a recurring false positive — `db dump --schema public` does not
-- include extensions, so the diff thinks pg_net is "missing" locally and
-- proposes dropping it. pg_net is required by Supabase internals; dropping
-- it would break Supabase services.
--
-- The same false positive was stripped from 20260502052239_remote_schema.sql
-- (see its header comment). We keep this file as a no-op so the local
-- migrations list stays in sync with the remote `supabase_migrations`
-- history table (which already recorded 20260507081133 as applied via
-- `db pull` repair).
--
-- Future `db pull` runs will likely regenerate this same drop line again.
-- Strip it the same way each time.
